the light turns off and on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can delay the repair of faulty airbag systems, potentially leading to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Owners received notification of the Takata airbag recall but were unable to have the repair done due to the unavailability of parts.

the light turns off and on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Torque converter failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, leading to loss of control or accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mount failure can cause the engine to move excessively, leading to premature wear on other engine components and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Broken engine mounts; engine mounts need to be replaced at low mileage (under 70
000 miles); worn and failed engine mounts.
